  "prompt": "What should be the Recruitment strategy cost for 6 months for a tech startup, which will include sourcing, banding, training, HRM, etc?",
  "response": "The recruitment strategy cost for a tech startup can vary widely depending on several factors. Here's a breakdown of potential costs for 6 months:\n\n1. Sourcing Costs:\n- Job boards (LinkedIn, Indeed, etc.): $1,000 - $5,000\n- Recruitment software/ATS: $2,000 - $10,000\n- Recruitment agency fees: 15-30% of annual salary per hire\n\n2. Employer Branding:\n- Digital marketing: $2,000 - $5,000\n- Career site development: $3,000 - $10,000\n- Social media recruitment: $1,000 - $3,000\n\n3. Recruiting Team:\n- In-house recruiter salary: $6,000 - $12,000/month\n- Freelance/contract recruiters: $50 - $150/hour\n\n4. Training & Onboarding:\n- Training programs: $2,000 - $5,000\n- Onboarding software: $1,000 - $3,000\n\n5. HR Management:\n- HR software: $1,000 - $5,000\n- HR personnel costs: $5,000 - $10,000/month\n\nEstimated Total Range: $30,000 - $100,000 for 6 months\n\nRecommendation: Budget 10-20% of total hiring budget for recruitment strategy.",
